Speaker of the Kwara State House of Assembly, Hon. Yakubu Danladi-Salihu, has kicked off his re- election bid to represent Ilesha- Gwanara constituency. Consequently, Danladi-Salihu has obtained an expression of interest and nomination forms to enable him re-contest for the legislative seat during the 2023 general elections. The vice chairman of All Progressives Congress (APCS) in the state, Hon. Abdullahi Sanmari, chairman of Baruten local government area, Hon. Abu Setraco and some personal aides of the speaker obtained the forms on his behalf. Danladi-Salihu has won the heart of his constituents with his sterling performance since he emerged as a young representative of the Ilesha/ Gwanara constituency at the Kwara State House of Assembly in 2019. Records showed that in the last three years, Danladi-Salihu has impacted significantly on the lives of his constituents with personally funded and facilitated projects ranging from basic amenities like roads, electricity, water, hospital, and schools as well as massive empowerment and appointments for his people. 